-- Bradesco Raised to `Buy' From `Neutral' at Bank of America on `Valuation'
-- Alexander Cuadros
-- 2010-07-07T11:51:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-07/bradesco-raised-to-buy-from-neutral-at-bank-of-america-on-valuation-.html

          
          
             Brazilian lender Banco Bradesco SA
was upgraded to “buy” from “neutral” at Bank of America
Corp., which cited the stock’s “attractive valuation.”  
 Bradesco will benefit from “a favorable macro scenario in
Brazil” and “strong operating trends,” Bank of America
analyst  Jorg Friedemann  wrote in a note to clients today.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
